                "name": "Krishnan Vasudevan",
                "href": "/profile/Krishnan-Vasudevan-6"
            },
            "answer_text": "If water first pass through an anion exchanger all the cations will convert to Hydroxides e.g Ca(OH)2, Mg(OH)2,NaoH etc. Because of Hydroxide the water pH will be high. Hence , calcium Hydroxide will be precipitated and block the exchanger. ",
